news.title: SC grants bail to SRS group's chairperson in Rs 770 crore fraud case
news.para: A bench comprising Chief Justice Sanjiv Khanna and Justice Sanjay Kumar observed that Jindal had been in jail for the last six-and-half years and the trial in the case was yet to begin.

news.title: Norway government eases loan-to-value mortgage limit to 90%
news.para: The revised rule set a maximum loan-to-value mortgage ratio of 90%, up from 85% previously, requiring borrowers to put up 10% equity when buying a home, down from 15% previously.

news.title: Illegal sand mining serious, needs to be curbed: Supreme court
news.para: The top court was hearing a 2018 PIL filed by one M Alagarsamy seeking a CBI probe into illegal sand mining in rivers and beaches in Tamil Nadu, Punjab, Madhya Pradesh, Maharashtra and Andhra Pradesh.

news.title: Telangana government launches 'BuildNow' for faster building and layout approvals
news.para: This will replace TG-bPASS (Telangana Building Permission Approval and Self-Certification System) introduced by the previous BRS govt in Sept 2020.

news.title: The future of office spaces: Embracing managed solutions for enterprises
news.para: According to a joint report by Table Space and Cushman & Wakefield, the footprint of flexible workspaces in India has expanded to 58 million square feet as of mid-2024, signaling a steady rise in the adoption of managed solutions.

news.title: Bombay HC slams misuse of petitions to delay redevelopment projects
news.para: A division bench of Justices A S Gadkari and Kamal Khata on November 12 dismissed a petition filed by a man, aged 67, refusing to vacate an 83-year-old bungalow where he has been living as a tenant since 1995.

news.title: Govt allocates 3.8 million houses under new PMAY-G norms this fiscal: Rural development minister
news.para: Chouhan said his ministry has spent a total of Rs 1.03 lakh crore so far this fiscal out of the budgeted Rs 1.84 lakh crore to meet commitments under various schemes.

news.title: Wells Fargo to move headquarters in San Francisco: Sources
news.para: The bank's corporate headquarters will continue to be in San Francisco and it has no plans to move out of the city, the bank said in an emailed statement to Reuters.

news.title: Austrian real estate tycoon questioned over Italian warrant
news.para: Benko, once one of Austria's richest men whose Signa empire crumbled in the largest insolvency proceedings in the country's history, was released after questioning in Innsbruck, according to a spokesman for prosecutors in the Austrian city.

news.title: AAI team identifies land parcel for proposed Srikakulam airport
news.para: A five-member team of officials from AAI visited Bidimi in Mandasa mandal and Anakapalli village in Vajrapukotturu mandal recently, and are learnt to have found the land parcel in the area suitable for the airport, which needs about 1,384 acres.

news.title: Intercement Brasil files for bankruptcy
news.para: The continuation of the talks to restructure debt and adjust capital structure "started to demand the filing of the request for bankruptcy," Intercement said.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad residents struggle with rise in pollution from construction sites
news.para: Baral said Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) vehicles are a rare sight and, as such, roads almost never get cleaned. This despite repeated complaints through the civic online grievance portal PCMC Smart Sarathi.

news.title: Patna: Owners can now upload their land details by February 2025
news.para: The state cabinet on Tuesday approved the govt's decision to give the owners an extended overall period of 180 working days for uploading the self-declarations.

news.title: Rajasthan government launches policy to promote manufactured sand units
news.para: An official said, the policy focuses on promoting the establishment of M-Sand units, streamlining their operations, making them investor-friendly, and providing support through the Rajasthan Investment Promotion Scheme (RIPS).

news.title: PMRDA seeks IIT Bombay and CoEP's help to inspect flats under PMAY scheme
news.para: This development comes after many residents approached PMRDA with complaints related to shoddy construction and issues with ceilings, bathrooms, and toilet leakages in their new flats within a year of possession.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body accelerates building plan approvals
news.para: Under the online building approval system introduced in 2016, permissions must be granted within 15 days, including notifying applicants of any deficiencies in their submissions.

news.title: Over 200 homestays deregistered in Almora for violating norms
news.para: The inspection reports revealed several violations, including inadequate safety measures, poor infrastructure maintenance, and discrepancies in registration processes.

news.title: Lucknow development body to expedite land acquisition for housing schemes
news.para: In the board meeting, decisions on land acquisition for different residential schemes, including IT City, Wellness City, Sitapur Road, and other areas, will be made.

news.title: Delhi government to pay Rs 8,000 aid to workers hit by construction ban
news.para: The construction ban was imposed on November 18 under the Graded Response Action Plan measure to check pollution.

news.title: Telangana government's revenue from property registrations rises 3% in November 2024
news.para: According to the chief minister's office, while the revenue through property registrations was 1,127 crore from 1.05 lakh documents in Nov last, the registration department received 1,160 crore from 1.19 lakh documents this Nov.
